sql:
SELECT team_id, SUM(wins) AS total_wins
FROM win_loss_records
GROUP BY team_id;

external_knowledge:
- "champions of seasons past" refers to teams that have the best performance metrics in a given season;
- "leading the pack" implies being ranked first in one of the performance categories: win percentage, points per game, rebounds per game, or assists per game;
- "secured the highest win rates" means having the highest win percentage in a season;
- "dominated in scoring, rebounding, and playmaking" refers to having the highest points per game, rebounds per game, or assists per game, respectively.

- 'High-scoring games' refer to games where a player or team scores 40 points or more;
- 'Rebounding games' refer to games where a player or team grabs 20 rebounds or more;
- 'Assisting games' refer to games where a player or team makes 20 assists or more;
- 'Stealing games' refer to games where a player or team records 5 steals or more;
- 'Blocking games' refer to games where a player or team records 5 blocks or more.

- `total_points` represents the sum of high game scores for each team;
- `total_mov` is the sum of the margin of victory for each team;
- `avg_wins` is the average number of wins across all records for each team;
- `avg_losses` is the average number of losses across all records for each team;
- `avg_win_percentage` is the average win percentage across all records for each team.

sql:
SELECT team_id, win_percentage
FROM win_loss_records
WHERE win_percentage > 0.5;

SELECT MAX(win_percentage) 
FROM win_loss_records 
WHERE season = 2022;

SELECT wins, win_percentage
FROM win_loss_records
ORDER BY win_percentage DESC;
